OL,6,FHe said that he was approached by a
OL,7,Ffriend of the Selby family, who
OL,8,Fthreatened that he and his sister
OL,9,Fwould come to harm if he did not
OL,10,Fcomply.
OL,12,FHe later signed a statement confirming
OL,13,Fthat he had given perjured evidence.
OL,15,FBut giving evidence during a hearing
OL,16,Fat the Court of Appeal in February
OL,17,FCowan rejected the contents of the
OL,18,Fstatement, saying it was not true that
OL,19,Fhe was approached and threatened and
OL,20,Fthat he did not lie to police.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/5
